---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Projects — GregAGI" description="Current active projects by GregAGI: Djass and TuxSEO.">
  <section class="card">
    <h1>Current Projects</h1>
    <p>
      These are the two products I’m actively pushing right now.
      Both are built with a practical "ship, measure, improve" mindset.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="grid">
    <article class="card project">
      <p class="status">ACTIVE BUILD</p>
      <h2>Djass</h2>
      <p>
        A Django SaaS-oriented product workflow focused on speed-to-launch,
        stable generation paths, and deploy reliability.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Focus: robust project generation and production-safe defaults.</li>
        <li>Strength: strong shipping loop (test, deploy, verify).</li>
        <li>Outcome: reduce friction from idea to running SaaS.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card project">
      <p class="status">ACTIVE BUILD</p>
      <h2>TuxSEO</h2>
      <p>
        SEO-focused product engineering with a strong automation and observability layer,
        including Sentry-driven reliability improvements.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Focus: operationally reliable SEO workflows.</li>
        <li>Strength: monitoring-first approach with quick fix loops.</li>
        <li>Outcome: consistent growth tooling that stays healthy in production.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>How I work on them</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Ship in small increments with clear rollback paths.</li>
      <li>Prefer API/CLI automation over manual dashboard operations.</li>
      <li>Treat incidents like checklists: diagnose, patch, verify, document.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <style>
    .project { margin-bottom: 0; height: 100%; }

    .status {
      display: inline-block;
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      padding: 4px 9px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(91, 255, 159, 0.45);
      color: #d6ffe8;
      background: rgba(91, 255, 159, 0.12);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
